headline: 3 Healthcare Stocks with Mounting Challenges
summary: From novel pharmaceuticals to telemedicine, most healthcare companies are on a mission to drive better patient outcomes. But speed bumps such as inventory destockings have persisted in the wake of COVID-19, and over the past six months, the industry has pulled back by 8.6%. This drop was discouraging since the S&P 500 held steady.
